    "feat": {
        "name": "Campfire Chronicler Dedication",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "You\u2019ve gained Isthralei\u2019s attention and can now offer stories up to him, either passing on your own stories or collecting those of travelers as he did. You become trained in Religion and Survival; for either of these skills in which you were already trained, you instead become trained in a skill of your choice. You gain the Offer Story action.   \n  \n**Activate** Offer Story;",
        "level": 2,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Archetype",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 12,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 452,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "52ef9cda2d54e07ee757696e4f8df79e",
                "text": "This feat belongs to an archetype."
            },
            {
                "name": "Dedication",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 41,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 215",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 215",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 215,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "d161ff4222f1e361de4583ab5e7afdee",
                "text": "Each archetype\u2019s dedication feat represents your character\u2019s dedicated effort learning a new set of abilities, making it impossible to split your focus and pursue another archetype at the same time. Once you take a dedication feat, you can\u2019t select a different dedication feat until you complete your dedication by taking two other feats from your current archetype. You can\u2019t retrain a dedication feat as long as you have any other feats from that archetype."
            }
        ],
        "archetype": [
            {
                "name": "Campfire Chronicler",
                "type": "feat_archetype",
                "link": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "Campfire Chronicler",
                    "alt": "Campfire Chronicler",
                    "game-obj": "Archetypes",
                    "aonid": 300
                }
            }
        ],
        "effect": "(auditory, concentrate, divine, linguistic, mental) You share a story of your travels with a creature within 30 feet. You gain the blessing of Isthralei as a +1 status bonus to AC and Will saves until the end of your next turn. On their next turn, the creature you shared a story with can take a single action, which has the auditory, concentrate, linguistic, and mental traits, to respond with their own story to gain the same benefits until the end of the following turn.",
